": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Solution Determination of the income from VuV of the spouses G"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "as with 51; however, advertising costs cannot be reduced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Since there is no blatant disproportion between the rent that is customary in the area and the rent actually paid, it can be assumed that the value of the transfer of use and the value of the consideration (rent) are balanced from an economic point of view (Item 54 a i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "According to this, it is a fully paid rental; Item 54 e is therefore not applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The one on the K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Any expenses incurred are deductible in full"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "In the 1984 income tax assessment for Ms. K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "no value in use is to be recorded (section 162 para 2 ESt\u00c4R 1984)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "53 Situation variant Situation as for 51; the one with mother K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The agreed rent per square meter is 3 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The first floor apartment is not a rented apartment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Section 21a, Paragraph 1, Clause 3, No. 1 of the Income Tax Act, because the agreed rent is grossly disproportionate to the local rent (Section 164b, Paragraph 13 of the Income Tax Act 1984)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The value in use of the apartment of the couple G"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "is therefore to be determined according to \u00a7 21a EStG (Section 164b, Paragraph 14, Clause 2 EStR 1984)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "To determine the income from the rented apartment, an excess calculation must be made"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Section 21a (5) sentence 2 EStG is no