a": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "are then to be determined overall by means of an income surplus calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Mrs K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "has to tax the difference between the local rent and the rent actually paid in accordance with Section 21 (2) second alternative EStG (Section 162 (2) ESt\u00c4R 1984 Item 54 a and Item 7)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Income tax assessment 1984 G"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Income from VuV rental value of own apartment10800-- DM Rental income 3600-- DM14400-- DM Advertising costs of own apartment (60 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "from 30,000 DM) 18,000 DM rented apartment (40 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "30,000 DM), of which 50 per cent is deductible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "(Item 54 e i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "35 a) 6000-- DM loss from VuV9600-- DMESt assessment 1984 K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Income from VuV (12 x 300-- DM) 3600-- DM6 \"Reserved\" right of residence not secured in rem 61 The couple Pfennig (P"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": ") on December 31, 1980 their daughter and son-in-law, the couple Sparsam (p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "), transfer their two-family house against the reservation of a lifelong right of residence to the apartment on the upper floor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "At the same time, the spouses S have undertaken to take over the debts on the property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of cost, the right of residence was not entered in the land register"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The couple S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "live in the apartment on the ground floor (150 sqm), the couple P live free of charge in the apartment on the upper floor (100 sqm)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The rental value of both apartments is 6 DM / sqm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The couple S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "have borne all costs of the property since the transfer of the house (in 1983 including depreciation DM 20,000)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Solution: For the non-in rem \"reservation\" right of residence, the provisions of Items 53 to 54 e (Item 5) apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The value in use of the apartment of the couple P"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "is to be assigned to these (Item 54), basically for all open assessments (Item 63)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "The couple S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "can those on the apartment of the couple P"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Do not deduct any property costs as income-related expenses (Item 54 d)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "A full deduction for income-related expenses is also not possible for assessment periods prior to 1984; The transitional regulations for the owner's expense allowance mentioned under 11 relate exclusively to rights of use in rem"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Income tax assessment 1983 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Income from VuV rental value own apartment10,800 DMlease value apartment parents0 DM total advertising costs 20,000 DM of which for upper apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": ") - 8000 DM12000 DMLoss from VuV1200 DMESt assessment 1983 P"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "Rental value of owner-occupied apartment (Item 54) 7200 DM62 Factual variant Facts as for 61; the spouses S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "and P"}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "apply in opposition proceedings against the 1983 ESt notification of the spouses S."}, {"meta": {"name": "0061693.xml"}, "text": "jointly the application of